data.text:
Brian T. Quinn resident of Lowell; age 43 LOWELL â€” Brian T. Quinn, age 43, a resident of Lowell, died unexpectedly on April 22, 2012 at Saints Medical Center.

Born in Lowell, MA on July 27, 1968, he was the son of the late John J. and Simone M. (Ayotte) Quinn, Sr.

He was a graduate of the Greater Lowell Regional Vocational Technical High School and was self-employed as a painter.

Brian was an avid dart player who enjoyed painting and spending time with his family and friends.

Surviving him are a sister, Lorrie Quinn-Filocamo of Sandown, NH; five brothers and four sisters-in-law, John J. Quinn, Jr. and his wife Milagro of Lowell, Michael Quinn and his wife Emily of Dracut, Anthony Quinn and his wife Donna of Lowell, Jeffrey Quinn and his wife Julie of South Carolina and Timothy Quinn of Lowell, his nieces and nephews, Darla, Johnny, Jeffrey Jr., Joshua, Jessica, Anthony, Richard, Ariel, Abby, Dalton to whom he was godfather, Dylan, Ryan, and Tyrell; also several aunts, uncles, cousins and dear friends.
